frameDefinitions: The answer to a Question is under discussion in a Group, which still  has a difference of opinion among its members.

A Factor affects the outcome of an Undertaking, which  can be a goal-oriented activity or the maintenance of a desirable state, the work in a Field, or something portrayed as affecting an Interested_party.
A concept, Concept_1, is related causally or collocationally to another concept, Concept_2 by means of some evidence.
A stretch of linguistic discourse or a Text that a Communicator produces has a Topic that it is about.
In this frame, a Booker brings about a situation where an Organization plans to provide Services to a Client at a particular Scheduled_time.
A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
frameExamples: Firstly, it is quite clear the <t>issue</t> in this context was not so much apostasy as much as it was treason.
Temperature is the most <t>critical</t> factor in successful storage.
We can <t>book</t> you a boatride on the Somme or a special tour of the Louvre .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Question</fen> is an open proposition the answer to which is under dispute.
The time interval during which the <fen>Question</fen> exists as a problem for the <fen>Group</fen>.
<fen>Factor</fen> is used for the concrete or abstract entity whose importance is assessed.
The <fen>Undertaking</fen> is a process or state or field of activity in which the <fen>Interested_party</fen> has a stake.
<fen>Interested_party</fen> identifies the people who are affected by a particular <fen>Factor</fen>.
A <fen>Factor</fen> may be generally important to the people or the activities in a field of endeavour.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Factor</fen> is important to the <fen>Undertaking</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Factor</fen> is important.
The concept which is linked to <fen>Concept_2</fen>.  Generally expressed as the external argument.
The concept which is tied to <fen>Concept_1</fen>.  Generally expressed as a PP complement.
The two concepts expressed jointly.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is what a <fen>Text</fen> is about.
A set of propositions that is coherent in being about a <fen>Topic</fen>
The <fen>Communicator</fen> is the person who has produced a <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Communicator</fen> produces <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The entity that is intended to receive the <fen>Services</fen> of the <fen>Organization</fen>.
The goods or labor that the <fen>Client</fen> requests the <fen>Organization</fen> preserve for future consumption or rendering.
The entity that enters into its records the request of the <fen>Client</fen> to retain <fen>Services</fen> in the future.
The future point in time when the <fen>Client</fen> arranges for the <fen>Organization</fen> to provide <fen>Services</fen>.
The entity that contacts the <fen>Organization</fen> directly.  In many if not most cases, a <fen>Booker</fen> is also a <fen>Client</fen>, but the roles may also be separated, e.g. a travel agent.
The time at which the reserving event takes place.
The location the <fen>Booker</fen> performs the action.
The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the Getting takes place.
listRoleExamples: The issue is <fex>who will have control of Iraq's rich oil resources</fex>.

The issue <fex>at the time</fex> was whether or not to relocate the Rennes-based part of
the team to California.
<fex>Being sure they are buying fresh food</fex> is important to most people.
Temperature is the most critical factor <fex>in successful storage</fex>.
Being sure they are buying fresh food is important <fex>to most people</fex>.
A successful GATT round is important <fex>for the world economy</fex>.
In his book, <fex>Smithers</fex> discusses cotton production.
Phil Collins booked his <fex>cockatoo</fex> into a $350-a-night pet hotel.
She reserved the room for the meeting <fex>for Tuesday</fex> .
The hotel reserved two rooms for me .
I booked the room for Monday <fex>only on Tuesday</fex> .
